    <note>Xiao(1) Dingji [723] Originally Tanzhou, Changsha xian residents. During the Ma(2) rebellion, one branch (Gu's [718]) moved to Linjiang, Xinyu xian, whereas Dingji's branch moved to Jizhou, Luling xian where his great grandfather served in the Southern  Tang administration. Neither his father nor grandfather held office. He was buried in Jizhou, Jian county. His grandson, Fu [3364], was the investigating censor that uncovered the innocence of Zhang(2) Liang's [7159] brother Yan's [3190] involvement in a counterfeiting conspiracy. Hu Quan, WJ, 29.23a. XCB, 133.11b; Wang Anshi, WJ, 89.920-922. CBD, 5, 4041-2.</note>
